<HEADLINE>
FISET THE LONE BRIGHT SPOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGER PHILLIPS  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL _ On a night of few positives for the Kings, at least
No.1 goalie Stephane Fiset got through a game without straining his
groin.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings' 3-1 loss to the Montreal Canadiens at the Molson
Centre on Monday night marked Fiset's first appearance in nearly
five weeks, and for much of the night, he kept his team in the
game. He'd left his previous two starts after suffering groin
strains.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't feel bad,'' said Fiset, who stopped 27 of 30 shots.
``Right now, maybe I'm a little bit tired.''
</P>
<P>
   Of Montreal's goals, one deflected past Fiset off the stick of
teammate Sean O'Donnell and two came when defensive mistakes by the
Kings resulted in outnumbered rushes by the Canadiens.
</P>
<P>
   But that was little consolation to Fiset.
</P>
<P>
   ``If we want to make the playoffs, we need to start winning some
games,'' he said. ``If we don't hurry, it's going to be too late.''
</P>
<P>
   Kings ransom: Forbes magazine performed a survey of the values
of the 104 teams in the NHL, Major League Baseball, the NBA and the
NFL. The Kings were ranked 17th among the 27 NHL teams, with a
value of $104 million. The Mighty Ducks were 14th at $109 million.
The Canadiens were seventh at $167 million.
</P>
<P>
   The most valuable NHL franchise is the New York Rangers at $195
million. The least valuable franchise in North American
professional sports is the Edmonton Oilers at $67 million. The
Kings are less valuable than all but two baseball teams (Montreal
and Minnesota) and two NBA teams (Milwaukee and the Clippers).
</P>
<P>
   Loose pucks: The game was the last for radio color commentator
Cammi Granato until Dec. 19 in St. Louis. Granato is leaving this
week to join the U.S. women's hockey team for an upcoming
tournament in Finland. The U.S. will compete against Canada and
Finland at the tournament. Granato captained the U.S. to an Olympic
gold medal earlier this year. Former King Daryl Evans will take
Granato's place on the air while she is gone.... Enforcer Matt
Johnson, suspended for 12 games by the NHL for a recent assault on
New York Rangers defenseman Jeff Beukeboom, traveled with the Kings
on this trip so he could visit his family in Ontario.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
