<HEADLINE>
SOURCES: JANKOVICH TO BE NORTHRIDGE AD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   NORTHRIDGE, Calif. _ Cal State Northridge insiders said former
University of Miami athletic director Sam Jankovich could be named
CSUN's acting athletic director as soon as today.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's what everyone's saying around the school,'' said one
insider, requesting anonymity. ``It's what everyone is expecting.''
</P>
<P>
   Jankovich couldn't be reached at his home for comment.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're not going to have any comment on that,'' CSUN spokesman
John Chandler said. ``Stay tuned. We'll have an answer on that
shortly.''
</P>
<P>
   Jankovich, who is retired, and CSUN President Blenda Wilson have
discussed such a move in the past. Jankovich, who hired Jimmy
Johnson at Miami and was a major fund-raiser at the school, has
been doing consulting work for Miami. He left Miami in 1990 to
become the chief executive officer for the New England Patriots
until January 1993.
</P>
<P>
   CSUN has been without an athletic director since Paul Bubb's
resignation took effect Nov. 6. Men's basketball coach Bobby
Braswell has served as administrator-in-charge of the athletic
department since then. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
