<P>
   RADIO-HELP _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ For years, Mildred _ her
funny Michigan accent and her elderly, sometimes fuzzy recollection
of history _ entertained and engaged listeners in the South Florida
area. One day last summer, a caller wanted to know where Mildred
had been _ she hadn't called the talk show in quite some time.
Mildred had been diagnosed with advanced ovarian cancer. After the
host of the radio show announced her diagnosis on the air, the
station's lines lit up with offers to help. One caller pledged
money to send Mildred's granddaughter to private school through
eighth grade. Dozens of listeners dropped by her room at Martin
Memorial Hospital, asking to see her. The radio station channeled
thousands of dollars in donations to a medical fund in her name.
(Houck, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TV-GHOST _ ATLANTA _ Don't adjust your TV screen. That wispy
shadow just may be the ghost of a Civil War soldier upset that
Atlanta's ABC affiliate, WSB-TV, recently plowed under some 1864
Confederate trenches. (Hendrick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
PHOTOS AND ILLUSTRATION. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TVSURFER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ NBC may announce lineup changes,
including a rumored move of ``Frasier,'' which might mean the more
highly rated ``Friends'' will get the 9 p.m. Thursday slot. Also
expected are sitcom shifts on Wednesday night. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
