   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   SIBLEY-COLUMN _ My friend Ann Waldon, a writer and very special
human being, is having a time with critics these days. Some like
her new book on Eudora Welty and some are tearing it and the author
apart. (Sibley, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VONFURSTENBERG _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Diane Von Furstenberg _
princess, world traveler, '70s wrap-dress creator and bearer of one
of the most recognized names on the planet _ sits down and talks
with Loretta Grantham. (Grantham, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY-JEKYLL _ Two ways to get the Christmas spirit in the
glow of candlelight _ in Jekyll Island's Millionaires Village and
in the charming village of Warm Springs. (Davis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) FREELANCER, not for use by NYT News Service.
ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
