<TEXT>
<P>
   ----------------- SALMAN RUSHDIE ------------------
</P>
<P>
   Spellbinder, man of letters, world citizen, champion of freedom
of expression and columnist for The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   Salman Rushdie has put his life on the line for his words. Now
the internationally acclaimed novelist is writing a monthly column
for The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   The first column, titled ``THE IMPERATIVE OF NATURAL JUSTICE FOR
CLINTON, HUSSEIN AND PINOCHET,'' can be found in your system under
category codes ``a'' general news and ``k'' commentary.
</P>
<P>
   Mr. Rushdie's reach is global (his books have been translated
into more than 30 languages). His perspective is unique.
</P>
<P>
   To get Salman Rushdie for your newspaper _ we have a charter
subscription rate for newspapers that sign up NOW _ contact one of
these New York Times Syndicate representatives: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (If you're in the Eastern time zone of the United States or
Canada, call BOB FARNELL at 1-800-535-4425. Or send a fax to him at
212-499-3382. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (If you're in the Central time zone of the United States, call
CONNIE WHITE at 1-800-444-0267. Or fax her at 816-822-1444. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (If you're in the Pacific or Mountain time zones of the United
States or in Latin America, call OLIVIA VASQUEZ at 310-996-0075. Or
fax her at 310-996-0089. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (If you're in Europe, Asia, Africa or the Middle East, call
