   CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee
approves a dramatic expansion of its impeachment probe to include
alleged financial irregularities in the 1996 Clinton re-election
campaign. Democratic committee members scoff at the Republicans'
plan to finish the panel's work by the end of the year. By MARK
HELM and DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
