suicide on television was widely disturbing, Americans are
increasingly sympathetic to the concept of helping the terminally
ill end their suffering and die with dignity. It's a tough call,
but anyone who has helplessly watched a loved one in needless pain
can understand what Kevorkian is trying to say. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
