<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-IMPEACH _ WASHINGTON _ House Judiciary Committee holds a
hearing on the consequences of perjury. (Carr, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COVERDELL _ WASHINGTON _ Sen. Paul Coverdell is re-elected to
the GOP Senate leadership as both parties select their senatorial
leaders. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DRAFT _ WASHINGTON _ Proving that the times they are a'changing,
four suburban high school seniors will race on computer keyboards
Wednesday to become the first young men to register on line with
the Selective Service. (Dart, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   TERM-LIMITS _ WASHINGTON _ The push for limiting terms of
Congress members to create a ``citizen legislature'' has lost
steam, as lawmakers who once pledged to quit after three terms are
refusing to renew that pledge as they reach senior posts. Among
them: Rep. J.C. Watts, R-Okla., and Rep. Tillie Fowler, R-Fla.,
both new members of the House leadership. (Malone, Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   AUDITS _ WASHINGTON _ Two audits of the Clinton campaign, two
audits of the Dole campaign and two other reports are to be
released simultaneously Tuesday at 2 p.m. EST by the Federal
Election Commission. Almost certainly, these are the long-rumored
audits in which FEC staff recommended that the Clinton campaign _
perhaps Dole's as well _ repay millions of dollars to the federal
treasury because of illegal activities in 1996. (Mollison, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY _ WASHINGTON _ Social Security Director Ken
Apfel speaks to the National Press Club on Tuesday, and a Social
Security study is released by Robert Reischauer, a former director
of the Congressional Budget Office, and Henry Aaron of the
Brookings Institution. Story combines both elements. (Lipman, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING _ WASHINGTON _ Consumers Union, publisher of Consumer
Reports magazine, holds a breakfast briefing to share tips to help
consumers save time, money and limit stress when shopping this
holiday season. (Monroe, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (l) lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Continuing spot coverage of the
Microsoft antitrust trial. (Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
