   INFANT FORMULA-BACTERIA &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Friendly bacteria that live in the human digestive
tract helping to absorb vitamins, minerals and other nutrients, may
soon be added to infant formulas. Probiotics _ good bacteria _
already are being used in some hospitals to help premature infants
better absorb nutrients and to control diarrhea. By CAROLYN POIROT.
Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
