   SWINDELL-BOOKSHELF &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Many years ago I read in, I believe, Reader's Digest,
a critical article written by, I believe, Clifton Fadiman, titled,
I believe, ``The Decline of Attention.'' The decline was in
attention to literature, more specifically toward ``serious''
fiction. The author, Fadiman or otherwise, was confident that the
impending death of seriously constituted fiction was a myth, and
gave evidence that such rumors had been alive for more than a
century. I was consoled then; but now I believe the decline is
real, has already happened, is near to bottoming out. By LARRY
SWINDELL. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   LOVETT-TEXAS SONGWRITERS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Lyle Lovett's recent two-CD set, ``Step Inside This
House,'' is a tribute to the Texas songwriters that influenced him.
But it wasn't just Lovett that fell under the spell of Guy Clark,
Townes Van Zandt and others: A whole generation found a home in the
homespun honesty of the music made in Austin and Houston in the
'70s. By DAVE FERMAN. Story has moved in ``e'' entertainment
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
