   BRIXTON BOUND &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It's Saturday morning, and the sun is shining as we
board the underground (subway) in Paddington, a predominantly
white, middle- to upper-middle class section of London. We're
headed for the 'hood _ Brixton. As African-American children of the
'80s, we couldn't NOT go to Brixton, immortalized by singers like
Eddie Grant and second-wave ska bands like the Specials. By JANETTE
RODRIGUES and NICHELE HOSKINS. Story will move in ``t'' travel
category. &QL; 
