world's stage, but in Southern California a combined Exxon-Mobil
barely registers a notice. That's because in the car-driving
capital of America, Mobil is one of a handful of players that fight
for the consumers' dollars and Exxon isn't even a factor. By
Gregory Wilcox.
</P>
