   JURY-SANCTIONS (Los Angeles) _ Albert Kyle was feeling a little
giddy as he exited the downtown Superior Court building early
Tuesday morning, thrilled to receive an order to return to jury
duty instead of a $1,500 fine. Out of 81 county residents ordered
to court for the first wave of a new sanctions program directed at
jurors who ignore their summons, 16 showed up, and all provided a
good enough excuse to escape the fine. By Peter Hartlaub. (Will
