Brian Brown occurred even though his patrol car contained
high-powered weaponry approved for officers after the North
Hollywood bank shootout. The higher-power firearms aren't suitable
for use by officers in a moving car, LAPD officials said Tuesday as
the Los Angeles Police Commission received a briefing on the events
that led to the officer's death. By Deborah Sullivan. (Will move in
the ``n'' California news file.)
