<HEADER>
A7621 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GA-GAS-DEREG-COX     12-01 0389
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GA-GAS-DEREG-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    62,000 gas users select new marketer
 &HT;    By Matthew C. Quinn
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ More than 62,000 Atlanta Gas Light Co. customers have
started buying gas from other companies now that they can choose
alternative suppliers.
</P>
<P>
   As of the start of the month Tuesday, 10 marketers were
supplying gas to homes and businesses previously served by Atlanta
Gas Light, said company spokesman Ross Willis. The total number of
customers who have switched amounts to about 4 percent of Atlanta
Gas Light's 1.4 million customers.
</P>
<P>
   More than 50,000 of the 62,000 who changed companies switched in
November, the first full month of competition under the state's new
natural gas deregulation law. Just 9,000 Atlanta Gas customers had
signed up with new marketers when sales officially began Nov. 1.
</P>
<P>
   When the new law is fully phased in, Atlanta Gas Light will
become a distribution company only and get out of the business of
selling gas.
</P>
<P>
   It will continue selling gas during its transition.
</P>
<P>
   Once 33 percent of Atlanta Gas Light's customers have chosen new
marketers; the rest will be assigned to marketers at random by the
Public Service Commission.
</P>
<P>
   In the meantime, the prices Atlanta Gas Light charges its
consumer and business customers are no longer controlled by the PSC
_ only the prices it charges marketers to deliver gas to their
customers.
</P>
<P>
   The company Tuesday posted December rates about 35 percent
higher for gas consumption than the company charged during
November. Charges for delivering gas are unchanged.
</P>
<P>
   Willis attributed the increased consumption charge to increases
in wholesale costs customary for high-demand winter months. The
average December bill of $82.54 includes an average gas consumption
charge of $60.68 plus delivery charges of $21.86. Willis said the
total is equivalent to last December's bills.
</P>
<P>
   The 10 marketers that have signed up customers as of Dec. 1 are:
SCANA Energy, Georgia Natural Gas Services, GasKey, United Gas
Management, Shell Energy Services, Columbia Energy Services, NorAm
Energy Management, e prime Peachtree Natural Gas and Infinite
Energy.
</P>
<P>
   Matthew C. Quinn writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
