   SCOTUS-SEARCHES (Washington) _ The Supreme Court rules that
short-term business guests have no constitutional protection
against unreasonable searches while in someone else's home. The
justices, in a 6-3 decision, reinstate the drug conviction of two
men whom a police officer, peering through a partially shaded
window without a search warrant, saw bagging cocaine. By STEVE
LASH. (Already filed.)
