   TEXAS-ESCAPE (Huntsville, Texas) _ Prison sources say that once
a death-row inmate attempts an escape, he is to be forever removed
from the work program. But that wasn't the case for convicted
killer Ponchai Wilkerson, who attempted to escape in 1993. He was
eventually put back on the work detail where he had the access to
try another escape. By KATHY WALT and ALLAN TURNER.
</P>
<P>
   ALCOHOL-VENDING (Austin, Texas) _ The attorney general has ruled
that the Alcoholic Beverage Commission cannot approve the use of
alcohol vending machines. The commission had earlier allowed an
Oklahoma City company to begin marketing machines that use a
personal identification number, despite a prohibition on the sale
of alcohol from coin-operated machines. By STEVE OLAFSON. (Already
filed.)
