suicide on television was widely disturbing, Americans are
increasingly sympathetic to the concept of helping the terminally
ill end their suffering and die with dignity. It's a tough call,
but anyone who has helplessly watched a loved one in needless pain
can understand what Kevorkian is trying to say. By MARIANNE MEANS.
(Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PERFECTION (Undated) _ The Denver Broncos are three-fourths
of the way toward accomplishing what only one other NFL team has
done in the history of the league _ go undefeated and untied during
the regular season. Denver would join the 1972 Miami Dolphins, who
went 17-0, including a Super Bowl championship, as the only teams
to complete a perfect regular season. By JOHN McCLAIN.
</P>
