   &UR; AMERICA'S FIRST CHRISTMAS CARD &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (900 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By PETER F. STEVENS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Did you even wonder, as your holiday greeting cards pile up, who
originated the idea that has turned into a megaindustry? Here's the
story of how in 1851 Richard H. Pease, an Albany, N.Y., shopkeeper
and skilled lithographer, decided to promote his shop with an
elaborately drawn holiday card. With photo of first card. (slugged:
BC-FIRST-XMAS-CARD-(HOLIDAYS)-ART-NYTSF, priority code r, category
code l)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SCRAPBOOKS: HOLIDAY GIFTS THAT WILL BE FAMILY TREASURES &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; (1,100 words) &QL; 
 &UR; By KATHY SENA &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Scrapbooking parties _ which turn family snapshots into family
heirlooms with a little bit of effort and imagination _ have become
the quilting bee of the '90s. And what better holiday gift than a
specially designed photo album? Sena gives simple instructions for
beginners to join the craze that is sweeping the nation. With great
art.
</P>
<P>
