u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-DOMINQUE-MOCEANU-HNS &LR;      12-01 0682
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DOMINQUE-MOCEANU-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JUDGE ORDERS OLYMPIAN'S PARENTS TO KEEP AWAY FROM COUPLE WHO
BEFRIENDED HER. 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By RON NISSIMOV 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the lastest twist to &UR;  &LR; an increasingly bizarre feud, a family
court judge signed a temporary restraining order Tuesday keeping
the parents of Olympic gold medalist Dominique Moceanu away from a
couple who befriended her.
</P>
<P>
   Dumitru and Camelia Moceanu were ordered to stay away from Brian
and Marcy Huggins, not to threaten the couple or to hire private
investigators to watch them.
</P>
<P>
   Brian Huggins, 32, provided construction equipment to build the
Moceanu gym in 1996 and helped Dominique get away from her parents'
Spring, Texas, home Oct. 17.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a shame things have gotten this far out of control with
people being threatened and people being stalked,'' Huggins said in
the Harris County Family Law Center while waiting with Dominique
and his attorney for the order to be signed.
</P>
<P>
   Dominique Moceanu said Monday that Houston police told her Nov.
13 that her father had negotiated with a man to kill Huggins and
her coach, Luminita Miscenco, 26. Miscenco, who was in Las Vegas
and not available for comment, also helped Dominique in her escape
from home. Dominique was granted a temporary protective order
Monday keeping her father away from her.
</P>
<P>
   Dominique, Huggins and his attorney Mike Moriarty, said they met
with Houston police Tuesday. They declined to discuss details of
the police investigation into the alleged threats but said the case
remains open for investigation.
</P>
<P>
   Although HPD spokesman Robert Hurst said Monday that the
investigation was closed for lack of evidence, Tuesday he said
``the case is being evaluated ... based on information brought
forth'' during the meeting between investigators, Huggins, Moriarty
and Dominique.
</P>
<P>
   Hurst declined to provide details of the investigation. &UR;
</P>
<P>
   &LR; Dumitru Moceanu has denied he was involved in any
murder-for-hire plot and says he has not harassed his daughter or
Huggins. The Moceanus were not present for either court proceeding
this week. Dominique's and the Huggins' request for temporary
protection were granted solely on the basis of affidavits they
filed.
</P>
<P>
   In his affidavit, Huggins said he believes he has ``been under
constant surveillance by people who (sic) I believe were hired by
Dumitru Moceanu.
</P>
<P>
   ``I believe that Camelia Moceanu is under the control and
direction of Dumitru Moceanu in their endeavor to wreak havoc on my
family and associates of her daughter, Dominique,'' the affidavit
said. ``I ... feel that the potential for bodily harm is as real
against my wife and my child as it is in the threats and the
activities of Dumitru against my person.''
</P>
<P>
   The Huggins are intervening in Dominique's case and both
requests for a permanent restraining order will be heard Dec. 9.
</P>
<P>
   The Moceanu's attorney Katherine Scardino said her clients have
a right to be concerned about Huggins because they believe Huggins
and Dominique, 17, are sexually involved.
</P>
<P>
   She said police told her that Huggins and Dominique were
recently in the Cayman Islands together and, ``I can only assume,
our contention is they did have a little thing going.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think an adult thinking about it could come to any
other conclusion,'' she said. ``A 32-year-old married guy with a
child hanging around girls and a gym, and a parent is not supposed
to get upset about that?''
</P>
<P>
   Huggins said Scardino's comments are false and typical of the
slanderous statements Dumitru has been making about him. His wife
echoed the sentiments.
</P>
<P>
   Huggins confirmed that he and Dominique went into hiding at a
tropical island after finding out about the alleged plot to kill
him, but denied that they are sexually involved. He said they did
not initially plan to go to the island but did so after being
offered free accommodations.
</P>
<P>
   Dominique said HPD officers told her to extend her trip for
safety reasons. She said her parents' accusations are absurd and
``pretty sad.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXEND OF STORY &QL;
</P>
