<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 2
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-JEWS-SETTLE-MONEY-NYT (moved on Saturday, Nov. 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, Nov. 28,
about Holocaust-related lawsuits misstated the Seagram Company
position of Edgar M. Bronfman Sr., who is president of the World
Jewish Congress. He is the company's chairman, not its former
chairman.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-SMITH-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Nov. 25)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Warren Hunting Smith, sent by the New York Times
News Service on Nov. 25, about the Yale University scholar, who
edited the letters of Horace Walpole, included an incorrect word in
a quotation from another Yale scholar who commented on Mr. Smith's
50-year effort. Frank Brady, chairman of the project that edited
the papers of James Boswell at Yale, said Mr. Smith's painstakingly
handwritten work in the days before computers was like being ``in
the scriptorium when Gutenberg came along,'' not ``in the
solarium.''
</P>
