<HEADLINE>
CONNECTICUT WOULD LOSE MONEY AS KRAFT GAINS, STUDY SAYS 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (a and s coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By TINA CASSIDY  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ A consultant's report on the feasibility of building a
$350 million stadium for the New England Patriots in Hartford,
Conn. concludes what some states and cities already know:
publicly-financed stadiums are money losers for many years for the
governments that build them, but can be very lucrative almost
