</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    No release of information in Piro murder
 &HT;    By Joe Brogan
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   RIVIERA BEACH, Fla. _ An autopsy was completed Tuesday on the
body of Janette Piro, wife of missing Singer Island resident
Christopher Benedetto, but the Palm Beach County medical examiner's
office did not release a cause and manner of death. Benedetto has
been missing since the couple broke a dinner date with neighbors
Nov. 11. Piro's body was found Nov. 23 in a freezer in the couple's
garage at 1160 Dolphin Road. Police are not releasing any more
details in the case, police Maj. David Harris said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Joe Brogan writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm Beach, Fla.
</P>
