of Technology, during an interview. Brown is the first woman, and
the first black, to head the college. Asked if she feels added
pressure to perform well she says: ``Being black is never
incidental. It's central to who I am. But I don't think F.I.T. set
out to make a statement about gender or ethnicity.'' (Marilynn K.
Yee/New York Times Photo)
