AIDS vaccine, near his tattoo of Roger, an ex-lover. In a step in
the long march toward eliminating one of the worst diseases the
world, Flinchum became the first volunteer in Atlanta to be
inoculated with AIDSVAX, the first vaccine for the AIDS virus to be
widely tested in the United States. (Jean Shifrin/New York Times
Photo)*LITE
</P>
