<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-01 22:43 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A7944 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-OROAMERICA-GAINS-LADN     12-01 0281
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-OROAMERICA-GAINS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THIRD QUARTER GOLDEN FOR OROAMERICA
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
BY ENRIQUE RIVERO  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The third quarter proved to be a golden period for
jewelry maker OroAmerica Inc., which experienced a healthy spike in
operating income despite overall lower earnings.
</P>
<P>
   According to figures released Tuesday, the company's sales for
the period ended Oct. 30 jumped 18 percent compared with the
comparable year-ago period to $54.6 million from $46.4 million.
</P>
<P>
   Although overall net income dipped 17 percent to $2.9 million
(or 46 cents per diluted share) from $3.5 million (56 cents),
operating income for the quarter actually increased 136 percent
when a one-time $4.7 million gain posted in the comparable year-ago
period is taken into account.
</P>
<P>
   According to company officials, operating income this quarter
was $5.2 million compared with last year's $6.9million. Without
that pretax gain from the settlement of litigation, however, last
year's operating income would have been $2.2 million.
</P>
<P>
   In addition, net income without the settlement would have
plunged to $933,000, or 15 cents per diluted share, in last year's
third quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Which all means that the company is operating more profitably
this time around, said Shiu Shao, the company's chief operating and
financial officer.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our gross profit margin improved significantly,'' he said,
adding it was 25 percent this quarter versus last year's 22.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The news sent OroAmerica stock up $1.25 Tuesday to close at
$10.25 _ its highest showing since Aug. 24, when it ended the day
at the same price.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-01-98 2243EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
