<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
USC PLAYERS NOT THRILLED WITH SUN BOWL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC was selected to play in the Sun Bowl on
Tuesday, and despite having missed out on postseason play for two
years, the news brought almost unanimous frowns from the Trojans.
</P>
<P>
   The game will probably be a rematch of USC's season opener, with
Purdue likely headed to El Paso for the New Year's Eve contest.
</P>
<P>
   USC's players had hoped for a trip to San Diego, but the Holiday
Bowl selected Oregon over the Trojans on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've heard some bad stuff about it because it's in El Paso,''
quarterback Carson Palmer said.
</P>
<P>
   The idea of playing the Boilermakers was nearly as unpopular
with the players as their destination.
</P>
<P>
   ``We already played that team. It's silly,'' linebacker Chris
Claiborne said.
</P>
<P>
   Purdue (8-4) will be USC's opponent, unless Ohio State is
selected for a BCS bowl game. The Buckeyes are not expected to be
an at-large team in the BCS bowls, however, leaving the
Boilermakers as the near-certain choice.
</P>
<P>
   In the slim event Purdue must head elsewhere, the Sun Bowl is
talking to Texas Tech, Mississippi and Texas Christian as backup
opponents.
</P>
<P>
   ``You're fortunate to go to a bowl game, you just hope you don't
have to go play the same team,'' defensive end Lawrence Larry said.
``Who wants to watch that game on TV? I would think that the
organizers would try to get another team.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Bowl seemed considerably happier about having the
Trojans (8-4) than the players, although as recently as Sunday, it
had hoped to avoid a USC-Purdue rematch.
</P>
<P>
   ``We had our eyes on USC from the beginning,'' said John Folmer,
executive director of the Sun Bowl. ``They draw so well for us.
They have a strong local following. This is a border community and
they like USC. They will also do a lot for us on TV.''
</P>
<P>
   USC played Michigan State in the 1990 Sun Bowl, then known as
the John Hancock Bowl. The game drew a near-capacity crowd of
50,562, and the Trojans lost 17-16.
</P>
<P>
   Ironically, the Sun Bowl was USC coach Paul Hackett's first game
as head coach. He was named interim head coach at Pittsburgh just
before the game, after then-coach Mike Gottfried was fired.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a great bowl. I like El Paso,'' Hackett said. ``It's a
positive experience because I've been there before. After two years
of not going anywhere, it's great.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett said he was unconcerned about playing Purdue twice in
the same season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't care. I don't think it's an issue,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Purdue is apparently also OK with the thought of a rematch.
Folmer said Boilermakers coach Joe Tiller said: ``That's good as
long as it's not 99 degrees (in El Paso). Then we have a chance.''
</P>
<P>
   When the teams played at the Coliseum in August, the temperature
was 118 degrees on the field. It should be about 50-60 degrees
cooler this time around.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's always tough to play a team twice, especially when you
win,'' Palmer said. ``They want revenge.''
</P>
<P>
   USC won the first meeting 27-17 as Palmer led a second-half
comeback.
</P>
<P>
   Although bowl bids were not expected to be firmed up until
Saturday, Folmer said so many bowls are worried about getting teams
they desire, that early invitations are being made. Folmer had
hoped to line up Miami as a possible opponent for the Trojans, but
the Hurricanes committed to the PC Micron Bowl in Miami on Tuesday,
to avoid being locked out of postseason play.
</P>
<P>
   He also talked to Virginia Tech, but the Hokies committed to the
Music City Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Hackett was happy to go to the Sun Bowl for another reason. The
Trojans will get more than enough practices because of the Sun
Bowl's late playing date of Dec. 31.
</P>
<P>
   Notes: USC offensive tackle Matt Welch suffered heart
palpitations during the Notre Dame game and was taken to a hospital
following the game. Hackett said he was awaiting test results and
was not sure if Welch would practice Friday, USC's first postseason
workout.... Wide receiver Windrell Hayes has a sprained big toe and
is on crutches but is expected to be available for the Sun Bowl....
Wide receiver Quincy Woods underwent knee surgery Tuesday and will
not return until spring practice.... Defensive tackle Matt
Childers, who is redshirting, underwent shoulder surgery Tuesday
and will also be out until the spring.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
