<HEADLINE>
TOLEDO GETS PAC-10 HONOR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Bob Toledo, UCLA's third choice to replace Terry
Donahue three years ago, was named Pac-10 Coach of the Year on
Tuesday, conference commissioner Tom Hansen announced.
</P>
<P>
   Toledo has directed the Bruins to 20 consecutive victories and
is one win from a probable date in the national championship game.
</P>
<P>
   This year, UCLA became the fourth team in the Pac-10 era (since
1978) to finish unbeaten and untied in conference play _ following
USC (1988), Washington (1991) and Arizona State (1996).
</P>
<P>
   The announcement came one day after eight Bruins were selected
to the All-Pac-10 team, including quarterback Cade McNown, who was
named co-offensive player of the year.
</P>
</TEXT>
